  "_comment": "Tasks granted on Progression Tree node unlock. Keyed by node_id. Each requirement is typed: { type: 'resource', resource, amount } (possession, consumed on Complete) or { type: 'building', building: '<BuildingType key>', amount } (cumulative builds, never consumed). A typeless entry with a 'resource' field is read as a resource requirement (legacy). Every requirement MUST be obtainable from that node's prerequisite closure (the node itself + all transitive prerequisites) or the player can soft-lock. CONVENTION (2026-06-24): every node that unlocks a building requires building it AND delivering the good it produces. Storage/Shelter/Bridge/Collection Point produce no good, so they are build-only. Building requirements count both manually-constructed buildings (construction-complete) and instant buildings like Collection Point/Road (counted on placement) — see TaskSystem._count_building. The Hearth (root) starts LOCKED; unlocking it grants the build-Collection-Point task as the player's first objective. Paving (ROAD) stays a plain delivery task for design reasons. See design/quick-specs/delivery-task-system-2026-06-20.md.",
